response: "{ \"title\": \"Easy: Sum of Cubes\", \"description\": \"Write a function `sum_of_cubes` that calculates the sum of the cubes of all integers from 1 to `n`, inclusive.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef sum_of_cubes(n: int) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `n` (int): The upper limit for the sum calculation, inclusive.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the sum of the cubes of all integers from 1 to `n`, inclusive.\", \"code\": \"def sum_of_cubes(n: int) -> int:\\n    total = 0\\n    for i in range(1, n+1):\\n        total += i ** 3\\n    return total\\n\", \"tests\": [\"assert sum_of_cubes(2) == 9\", \"assert sum_of_cubes(10) == 3025\", \"assert sum_of_cubes(1) == 1\", \"assert sum_of_cubes(3) == 36\"] }"
